cool stuff in the form of Leopard

00:06:10.519 --> 00:06:13.069
and various other things we have happening during the week.

00:06:13.069 --> 00:06:16.110
And really remember, we're human.

00:06:16.110 --> 00:06:20.360
We're engineers at Apple, but a year ago, I
was a student like yourself just graduating

00:06:20.360 --> 00:06:22.610
from college and here I am working here now.

00:06:22.610 --> 00:06:24.259
And we're always eager to answer your questions.

00:06:24.259 --> 00:06:28.629
For a lot of engineers throughout the week, this is
the high point of being able to deal with everyone

00:06:28.629 --> 00:06:31.569
and seeing the people who are actually
using the technologies

00:06:31.569 --> 00:06:34.129
and those who are really excited
about the things that are being done.

00:06:34.129 --> 00:06:37.000
So don't be bashful, get in there an ask questions.

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:39.560
Really dive deep with this.

00:06:39.560 --> 00:06:43.259
So this is a really exciting time for us to work at Apple.

00:06:43.259 --> 00:06:47.399
Apple's one of the top 10 most valued brands.

00:06:47.399 --> 00:06:55.049
We have over 100 million iPods we've sold, stock's at an all
time high, and we have over 500,000 developers registered

00:06:55.050 --> 00:06:59.050
with the ADC, all of which you guys are a part of.

00:06:59.050 --> 00:07:06.050
And the real key with this is that you
guys are the future of the platform.

00:07:06.050 --> 00:07:12.360
There are awesome applications coming out these days written
by people just like you, who really understand what it is

00:07:12.360 --> 00:07:17.759
to be a Macintosh programmer, understanding
the user interaction side of things.

00:07:17.759 --> 00:07:24.620
Whether that's Checkout, Coda, Delicious Library, or any one
of the really awesome new applications that are coming out,

00:07:24.620 --> 00:07:31.800
the real focus is on the user and we're counting on
you guys to really help drive us forward as a platform.

00:07:31.800 --> 00:07:35.310
So now to do that, we have tons happening this week.

00:07:35.310 --> 00:07:38.750
We've got six tracks, whether you're
looking for the Mac OS X essentials.

00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:43.040
So most of the foundational technologies,
Leopard innovation, a lot of the new things

00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:48.500
